==English==
===Etymology===
From Ancient Greek άμαρτία (''hamartia''), meaning ''[[error]]'' or ''[[failure]]''.  From the verb ''hamartanein'', "to miss the mark".

===Noun===
'''hamartia'''

#The [[fatal]] [[flaw]] of a [[literary]] [[tragic]] [[hero]]
#*Macbeth's '''hamartia''' was ungodliness.
#(''Christian theology''): [[sin]]

